{
  "texts": [
    "The discussion of integrating GAI in the peer review process is growing across the academic community.",
    "Various studies discussed the role of ChatGPT that could play in streamlining this critical process (Biswas et al., 2023; Carabantes et al., 2023; Checco et al., 2021; Saad et al., 2024).",
    "Findings indicate that it can perform tasks like automating initial screenings and assessing the quality of manuscripts which could significantly lighten the load on reviewers.",
    "Additionally, there is potential to provide feedback on manuscripts (Checco et al., 2021) and maintain structural and content quality with academic standards (Abdelhafiz et al., 2024; Zohouri et al., 2024).",
    "Despite these advantages, the current technical limitations of the GAI tools cannot replace human reviewers due to the lack of understanding of complex contexts (Carabantes et al., 2023; Zohouri et al., 2024)."
  ]
}